  "body": "Here is an example contract that triggers the bug when one of the public functions is called with `0` as the argument.\r\nAny other value will work.\r\n\r\n* Remix Version: `0.23.0` (latest), bug was not triggered by earlier versions.\r\n* Solidity Compiler Version: `0.8.13` (latest)\r\n* Deployed on JavaScript VM\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.0;\r\n\r\ncontract AssignZeroBug {\r\n    address private addr = 0xAb8483F64d9C6d1EcF9b849Ae677dD3315835cb2;\r\n    uint private number = 1;\r\n\r\n    function assignAddress(address _addr) public {\r\n        addr = _addr;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function assignNumber(uint _number) public {\r\n        number = _number;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nExample error message:\r\n```\r\ntransact to AssignZeroBug.assignNumber errored: base fee exceeds gas limit (vm hf=berlin -> block number=6 hash=0xd5a3bf59ba95d1f81b8b302e662b4bdc46063883fe79bdeb124da677e858f838 hf=berlin baseFeePerGas=none txs=1 uncles=0 -> tx type=0 hash=0x53b8a5c103d242f0911fbf51beba7c9ecf532b8129317d3f38fe617521e25541 nonce=4 value=0 signed=true hf=berlin gasPrice=1)\r\n```\r\nGas limit was set to `3000000` in Remix.",
